Mesosoma

. Pronotum dorsolaterally imbricate, laterally and ventrolaterally polished with transverse wrinkles; epomia absent; mesoscutum finely punctate; scutellum and post scutellum densely covered with setae; mesopleuron dorsolaterally foveolate with strong transverse wrinkles and covered with sparse setae (
Fig. 3B
); speculum denudate with transverse wrinkles; epicnemial carina present reaching only basal part of mesopleuron; mesopleuron ventrolaterally foveolate without wrinkles and sparse setae; sternaulus absent; posterior transverse carina of mesosternum straight not produced near the coxal area; metapleuron punctate and with its posterior part densely covered with setae; juxtacoxal carina complete with perpendicular carinae vestigial; juxtacoxal area imbricate; pleural carina complete; spiracle elliptical with its width 0.36–0.62× the spiracle height; propodeum hairy and foveolate; strong transverse wrinkles between petiolar area and posterior part of areola; vestigial wrinkles between middle part of areola and basal area (
Fig. 3B
); lateral longitudinal carina of propodeum incomplete not reaching propodeum neck; median longitudinal carina of propodeum complete; propodeum neck 0.6–0.8× the size of hind coxa.

Metasoma
. Tergites imbricate; first tergite with sparse setae, first sternite glabrous with subpetiolar process inconspicuous; tergite II 0.77–0.87× the length of tergite I; remaining tergites and sternites finely punctate covered with small setae; thyridium tear-shaped (
Fig. 3E
); ovipositor sheath covered with long setae; ovipositor straight (
Fig. 3F
), 1.0– 
1.14 mm
long; ovipositor notch distant from apex 0.19–0.23× length of ovipositor; ovipositor deep (
Fig. 3G
) notch angle 90º–105º; ovipositor ventral valve with a lobe near apex.
